<%# Locals: book (required), user (required), all_shelves (optional),
    member_ids (optional).

    A floating "+ shelf" button + picker panel designed for grid cards
    on the library index where the full chip_row would be too dense.
    Reuses the existing shelf-picker Stimulus controller and
    picker_panel partial; toggles update the panel rows in place via
    the same turbo_streams as chip_row.

    The button itself sits in a relative wrapper so its panel
    positions correctly. Caller (book card) decides where to absolute-
    position the wrapper. %>
<div data-controller="shelf-picker" class="relative">
  <button type="button"
          data-action="shelf-picker#toggle"
          title="Add to shelf"
          aria-label="Add this book to a shelf"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-white/70 hover:bg-white focus:bg-white border border-stone-200/70 hover:border-stone-300 text-stone-600 hover:text-stone-900 shadow-sm transition cursor-pointer">
    <svg class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
      <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4"/>
    </svg>
  </button>

  <div data-shelf-picker-target="panel"
       class="hidden absolute top-full right-0 mt-1 w-64 bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-md shadow-lg z-20">
    <%= render "shelves/picker_panel",
          book: book,
          user: user,
          **local_assigns.slice(:all_shelves, :member_ids) %>
  </div>
</div>
